                                    <blockquote class="homequote"><p>“One of the most valuable skills in our economy is becoming increasingly rare. If you master this skill, you’ll achieve extraordinary results.”</p></blockquote>
<h3>Now Available!</h3>
<p>In <em>Deep Work</em>, author and professor Cal Newport flips the narrative on impact in a connected age. Instead of arguing distraction is bad, he celebrates the power of its opposite: the ability to focus intensely on cognitively demanding tasks; a skill he calls “deep work.”</p>
<p><em>Deep Work</em> is an indispensable guide to anyone seeking focused success in a distracted world.</p>
<p class="morebutton"><a title="Deep Work: Rules for Focused Success in a Distracted World" href="http://calnewport.com/books/deep-work/">More about Deep Work</a></p>
<div class="separator2"></div>
<div class="homeblock">
<h2>Available Now:</h2>
</div>
<p><a href="/books/so-good/"><img class="alignleft" src="/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/so-good-they-cant-ignore.jpg" alt="So Good They Can't Ignore You" /></a></p>
<h2>So Good They Can&#8217;t Ignore You: Why Skills Trump Passion in the Quest for Work You Love</h2>
<p>In this eye-opening account, Cal Newport debunks the long-held belief that &#8220;follow your passion&#8221; is good advice. Not only is the cliché flawed—preexisting passions are rare and have little to do with how most people end up loving their work— but it can also be dangerous, leading to anxiety and chronic job hopping.</p>
<p><a title="So Good They Can’t Ignore You: Why Skills Trump Passion in the Quest for Work You Love" href="http://calnewport.com/books/so-good/">Read more »</a></p>
<div class="separator2"></div>
